{
  "stem": "18778.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 274.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They riffled through all kinds of papers and they said well, the B'nai Brith, this was a subversive organization as far as they were concerned and so on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they-- they dragged him off to jail.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think all the men in town were first brought to the local jail.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "From there, most of them were shipped to concentration camps, either Dachau-- I think for most of our area, it was Dachau, which is near Munich, not close by at all.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "However, my father was known at the jail, because as an attorney he often had clients in jail whom he visited.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so they kept him and they treated him kindly, thank God.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They kept them in jail.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There were a handful of others as well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But most of the men and boys, up to-- from age 14 on, were shipped to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Eventually, a policeman, as I had said before, called my mother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I'm not quite sure how long he was in jail.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It might have been as much as six weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He finally came out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My mother had begged him not to go to the house, but to come directly to the house where she was staying.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She was staying with friends in a-- about a couple of blocks away from where we lived.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But he did go to the house first.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I think he was just absolutely devastated with what he saw.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then he-- he came to my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And from then on, it was-- the only thing was to get ready to get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't stay.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They'd come for a visit for-- come Saturdays, leave Sundays to visit with me.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
